      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "DONMARO NZ (6) is a newcomer to the Andy Gath yard from NZ. Has had four-and-a-half months off since he last raced at Addington but was readied with a trial win and generally comes to hand very quickly, with three wins from five first-up appearances. Can kick off with a win. MADRIGAL NZ (4) is in good form having placed in two Victorian runs since winning in SA. Finished third at her latest appearance at Ararat, beaten 4.5 metres. Can make an impact again. TARA VICTORY NZ (5) is up in grade but has put two wins together and usually races well at this distance so respect. TEN DA TOUCH NZ (7) starts from out wide but is in the mix after drawing on the back row finishing third at Shepparton last time out.",
